Consistently use [[ .. ]] to test strings or files, (( .. )) to test numbers or arithmetics and ''if COMMAND'' to test exit status. Do *NOT* use [ .. ] in bash, *only* in sh. See http://mywiki.wooledge.org/tests and http://mywiki.wooledge.org/BashGuide/TestsAndConditionals. Also see http://mywiki.wooledge.org/BashFAQ/031 for the difference between [ and [[
